    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cor.00001.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey</name>
                    <date when="1886-04-13">April 13 '86</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My Dear Prof: Carson</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Yours <choice><orig>rec'd</orig><reg>recieved</reg></choice><ptr target="cor.00001_n1"/>&#8212;The copy of John Burroughs's <hi rend="underline">Notes</hi><ptr target="cor.00001_n2"/> I send
                to you by same mail with this.&#8212;The price is $1 which you may just enclose in
                envelope &#38; mail to me here&#8212;I too <choice>
                    <orig>enjoy'd</orig>
                    <reg>enjoyed</reg>
                </choice> the young man's Woodruff's visit to me &#38; talk<ptr target="loc.01336_n1"/>&#8212;&#38; hoped to have
                seen you&#8212;I am <choice>
                    <orig>ab't</orig>
                    <reg>about</reg>
                </choice> the same in health &#38;c&#8212;(nothing at all to brag of)&#8212;I read
                publicly my <hi rend="underline">Death of Abraham Lincoln</hi> next Thursday in <choice><orig>Phila</orig><reg>Philadelphia</reg></choice>:</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cor.00001.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text> 
